On 11/6/04 5:29 AM, "Wayne" <mga60(-at-)optonline.net> wrote:

> Has anyone seen an oil drain plug that had an allen wrench hole in it?

Yep. Some of the engine seems to have them and some don't. Mine is original:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Maintenance2/226-OilChange.jpg

I don't know why people have such trouble with this plug. Even the one I
found at the junkyard today looked like someone had tried to remove it with
a chisel.

> Any
> thoughts how to get my out so that I can put in a "proper" plug in so that
> during future oil changes I can get it out with an opened-ended or box-ended
> wrench?

The correct tool for the job is an 8mm hex bit on the end of your ratchet.
Works everytime.

